de.hsos.ecs.richwps.wpsmonitor.control.scheduler

Class JobFactoryService

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.hsos.ecs.richwps.wpsmonitor.control.scheduler.JobFactoryService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.quartz.spi.JobFactory

    public class JobFactoryService
extends Object
implements org.quartz.spi.JobFactory
    Only one JobFactory can be registred in Quartz at the same time. However the WpsMonitor uses factories to inject all necessary dependencies into the new objects. This approach is also used at new Job instances. So the JobFactoryService, which implements the JobFactory interface, stores other JobFactory instances and delegates the newJob-calls to the right registred JobFactory instance. The right JobFactory instance is identified by the Job.class Class. If no JobFactory is registred for a specific job, then SimpleJobFactory is used. SimpleJobFactory is the default behavior of Quartz.
    Author:
    Florian Vogelpohl
